For every element X in nums1:

Find X in nums2
Start checking elements AFTER that index
The first greater element is the answer
If none exists → -1

Example 1:

Input: nums1 = [4,1,2], nums2 = [1,3,4,2]

Output: [-1,3,-1]

Approach:
1. Second Arr -> push to stack and check whether next element is greater
- if found greater remove top element and map it e.g -> 1->3  (since current element 3 is greater than stack top 1)
2. compare with First array -> and if value do not exist in map set -1 against the current element
- e.g if 4 not consist in map then 4 -> -1

Solution:
class Solution {
    fun nextGreaterElement(nums1: IntArray, nums2: IntArray): IntArray {
        val result = IntArray(nums1.size)
        val stack = ArrayDeque<Int>()
        val map = mutableMapOf<Int,Int>()

        for(i in nums2){
            // remove top if current element is greater and map 
            while(stack.isNotEmpty() && i > stack.last()){
                val removed = stack.removeLast()
                map[removed] = i // map top element with current
            }
            stack.addLast(i)
        }
       
        for(i in nums1.indices){
            result[i] = map[nums1[i]] ?: -1 // if not exist in map set -1
        }
        return result
    }
}
